org.jcvi.jillion.core.residue.aa

Interface ProteinSequence

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Iterable<AminoAcid>, ResidueSequence<AminoAcid,ProteinSequence,ProteinSequenceBuilder>, Sequence<AminoAcid>, Serializable

    public interface ProteinSequence
extends ResidueSequence<AminoAcid,ProteinSequence,ProteinSequenceBuilder>, Serializable
    ProteinSequence is a marker interface for Sequences that contain AminoAcids.
    ProteinSequence is Serializable in a (hopefully) forwards compatible way. However, there is no guarantee that the implementation will be the same or even that the implementation class will be the same; but the deserialized object should always be equal to the sequence that was serialized.
    Author:
    dkatzel

        default String toString(Function<AminoAcid,String> toStringFunction)
        Convert this sequence into a String using the user defined function to write out each AminoAcid.
        Specified by:
        toString in interface Sequence<AminoAcid>
        API Note:
        for example, to print each amino acid by its 3 letter code instead of the one letter code: 
          sequence.toString(AminoAcid::get3LetterAbbreviation)
        Parameters:
        toStringFunction - The Function to convert each amino acid into a string. If the function returns null, then that amino acid is not included in the resulting output String.
        Returns:
